Definition: planning prudently for the future
Example: large goals that required farsighted policies; took a long view of the geopolitical issues
Synonyms: farsighted, noun, cognition, farsightedness, foresighted, attribute, foresightedness, foresightful, foresightfulness, prospicient, prospicience, long, longsighted, planning, prudently, for, the, future, large, goals, that, required, policies, took, a, view, of, geopolitical, issues
Category: adj.all
